message: It was fixed an incomplete and possibly misleading information so the introduction can be as clear as possible about the agreement that led him to Man United.

Improvement in the introductory paragraph: the whole pack of agreement between Man United and Sporting Lisbon in the introduction and details in the due section, this makes more since than picking up just one of the agreement details to put in the introduction.

correction in the currency used in the text. The agreement was made in Euros, Manchester United will pay in Euro the upfront and the further add-ons, according to Sporting Lisbon's official report to CMVM (Portugal's regulatory body). So there is no point in putting the value in sterling pound, even the former source appointed by the text (BBC Sports) reports all values in Euros. Besides, it was fixed a huge lack of information about full values involved in the agreement.

message: cited quote in no way implies that Wittgenstein seriously contemplated a literal resurrection of jesus and it is misleading to say that he did. Chapter 6 of the Tractatus is clearly opposed to a classic Christian concept of faith and he remarked to Russell in the 1910s that he had a vitriolic attitude towards christianity. Wittgenstein was also obsessed with Tolstoy's "On the Gospels" during his service in ww1, further evidence against a literal interpretation of Jesus' resurrection. doc
